The paper discusses a query algorithm for selecting a subset of a database that minimizes regret ratios for a family of infinite utility functions. This involves modeling individuals' preferences and decision-making processes, which is a common theme in databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a heuristic algorithm and discusses query properties, which are relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
